<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="243" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,855,1134]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,318,927,953]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A member of the “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1926" box="[525,671,927,953]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Bulgarosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,671,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Bulgarosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” complex (characterized by the presence of a strongly developed, posterior, medial syncolpocoxite of the anterior gonopods). Most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Curcic &amp; Makarov 2008" authorityName="Curcic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2008" box="[1017,1436,963,992]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Belbogosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1166,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Belbogosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curcic, B. P. M. &amp; Makarov, S. E. &amp; Tomic, V. T. &amp; Mitic, B. M. &amp; Curcic, S. B. &amp; Dudic, B. D. &amp; Lucic, L. R. &amp; Jasnic, N." box="[1171,1436,963,992]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref5579" refString="Curcic, B. P. M., Makarov, S. E., Tomic, V. T., Mitic, B. M., Curcic, S. B., Dudic, B. D., Lucic, L. R. &amp; Jasnic, N. (2008) On a new genus of endemic millipedes (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida Anthroleucosomatidae) from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1743, 1 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1743.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">Ćurčić &amp; Makarov 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Curcic, B. P. M. &amp; Makarov, S. E. &amp; Tomic, V. T. &amp; Mitic, B. M. &amp; Curcic, S. B. &amp; Dudic, B. D. &amp; Lucic, L. R. &amp; Jasnic, N." box="[158,355,999,1028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref5579" refString="Curcic, B. P. M., Makarov, S. E., Tomic, V. T., Mitic, B. M., Curcic, S. B., Dudic, B. D., Lucic, L. R. &amp; Jasnic, N. (2008) On a new genus of endemic millipedes (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida Anthroleucosomatidae) from the Balkan Peninsula. Zootaxa, 1743, 1 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1743.1.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Ćurčić 
<emphasis box="[239,293,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
) mainly in the shape of certain structures of anterior gonopods, namely the bifurcate medial process of syncolpocoxite. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Makarov &amp; Curcic" authorityYear="2012" box="[492,648,1035,1061]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Dazbogosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[492,648,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Dazbogosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curcic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2008" box="[920,1068,1035,1061]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Belbogosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[920,1068,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Belbogosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pair of distinctive lateral processes of the anterior gonopod syncolpocoxite directed laterad and slightly curving cephalad. Angiocoxites of the posterior gonopods are distally tapering, and curving subtly in the genus 
<emphasis box="[941,1127,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Makarov &amp; Curcic" authorityYear="2012" box="[941,1098,1107,1133]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Dazbogosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dazbogosoma</taxonomicName>
vs
</emphasis>
sigmoid in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curcic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2008" box="[1255,1403,1107,1133]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Belbogosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1403,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Belbogosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
